                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>Following the national election on November 4, 1952, the <persName
                        corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName> administration began active cooperation
                    with representatives of President-elect <persName corresp="#p_EDD1">Dwight D.
                        Eisenhower</persName> to assure a smooth administrative transition. The
                    climax of this cooperation came on November 18, 1952 when the President-elect
                    met with President <persName corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName> at the White
                    House. Korea was a prominent issue both in the background papers and proposals
                    leading to the White House meeting, and during the meeting itself. For
                    documentation on efforts to assure a smooth administrative transition regarding
                    foreign policy, during November 1952–January 1953, see <ref
                        target="frus1952-54v01p1#pg_1">volume I, Part 1, pages 1</ref> ff.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
